  "bezeichnung": "English: The World of Science",
  "kreditpunkte": 4,
  "lernziele": "<p>This module is suitable for students of levels B2 to C1.<br />Students will develop their ability&nbsp;to communicate in a technical and academic environment. They will know how to write</p>\n<ul>\n    <li>academic papers (abstract, introduction, methods, results, discussion and conclusion sections) </li>\n    <li>feasibility studies </li>\n    <li>research papers </li>\n    <li>environmental impact studies </li>\n    <li>reports </li>\n    <li>business and academic proposals </li>\n</ul>\n<p>Students will also be able to actively participate in all technical discourse situations.&nbsp;</p>",
  "semesterBewertung": "Note von 1 - 6",
  "sprache": "de-CH",
  "zustand": "deaktiviert",
  "kurse": [
    {
      "id": 28072,
      "kuerzel": "EnglScience",
      "bezeichnung": "English: The World of Science",
      "planinhalt": "<p>Students will revise their general knowledge of English in a variety of task-based situations focused on the practical needs of engineers. The course is based on a script which contains the foundations of academic writing and also includes topical and exciting material from the world of technology. Students develop their specialist vocabulary on the basis of a self-study task which relates to their core subject. Students also receive the necessary input to pass the widely recognized academic IELTS exam, whereby international student mobility is fostered.</p>",
